A CV-screening system used for recruitment/employment decisions is a high-risk AI system under EU AI Act Annex III §4(a), triggering obligations in Arts. 9–15 (risk management, data governance, transparency, human oversight, logging, accuracy/robustness) plus registration and conformity assessment. The key verifiable property to enforce is non-discrimination / demographic-parity-style fairness on protected attributes: a measurable bound on disparate impact across gender, age, ethnicity, and disability, e.g. selection-rate ratio between any protected and reference group ≥ 0.8 (four-fifths rule) and statistical-parity difference ≤ ε on a held-out audit set, continuously monitored and logged per Art. 12. This is testable on labeled audit data, reproducible, and auditable by the provider and notified body.
